# RPTR bounce buffer: software signal completion for no-atomics platforms
#
# On platforms without PCIe AtomicOps (e.g. Westmere Xeon), GFX8 CP signal
# writes to system memory use PCIe AtomicOp TLPs which the root complex drops
# silently.  The read_dispatch_id (RPTR) still advances after packet processing,
# so we can detect completion from CPU.
#
# This patch adds a per-queue bounce buffer that:
# 1. Scans newly submitted AQL packets for completion_signal fields
# 2. Monitors read_dispatch_id for completion
# 3. Decrements signals from CPU when the CP has processed the packet
#
# Also forces polling-based signal wait (HSA_ENABLE_INTERRUPT=0 equivalent)
# on no-atomics platforms, since event mailbox writes fail the same way.
#
# Depends on patch 0003 which adds no_atomics_ field and NoPlatformAtomics().
#
# Signed-off-by: David Connolly <david@connol.ly>

